'''International election standards''' are a set of principles and implementation guidelines for elections which have basis in the public international human rights law instruments.<ref>{{cite web |title=DRI: International consensus Essential elements of democracy |url= http://democracy-reporting.org/files/essential_elements_of_democracy_2.pdf |work=democracy-reporting.org |accessdate= 10 July 2014}}</ref> Sources of these standards are international (universal and regional) treaties, international customary law, political commitments, internationally agreed principles of good practice adopted by governmental and non-governmental organisations. <ref>{{cite web |agency= The Carter Center, Election Obligations and Standards Database|url = https://eos.cartercenter.org| title = Election Standards &#124; the Carter Center}}</ref>
==International treaty standards== [[International treaty]] standards are agreements made by states voluntarily. Treaty monitoring body is responsible for monitoring the compliance of these standards. The most important treaty in setting the fundamental standards in elections is considered to be the [[International Covenant on Civil and Political Rights]].
